comments: Little (POR) moves forward into Brown's (BOS) body and initiates contact that dislodges him from his legally obtained position.
Langford (BOS) is already in Simons' (POR) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Covington (POR) legally contests Williams' (BOS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Nurkic (POR) briefly grasps Williams III's (BOS) jersey and immediately releases his jersey as Williams III jumps for the rebound.
Tatum (BOS) legally contests Little's (POR) shot near the rim.
Nurkic (POR) is already in Brown's (BOS) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Williams (BOS) legally contests Simons' (POR) jump shot attempt.
Williams III (BOS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Nurkic (POR).
McCollum (POR) moves laterally into Brown's (BOS) path, and the contact occurs prior to Brown's gather.
Nurkic (POR) is already in Tatum's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
McCollum (POR) is bracing for the contact from Williams III (BOS) and releases away from the contact.
Brown (BOS) is already in Covington's (POR) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Nurkic (POR) steps forward into Tatum's (BOS) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.
Nurkic (POR) is already in Langford's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Simons (POR) is bracing for the contact from Williams III (BOS) and releases away from the contact.
Nurkic (POR) remains stationary on the floor and does not turn into Williams III's (BOS) body as he contests Simons' (POR) shot.  Williams III's momentum causes him to move forward towards Nurkic.
Williams III's (BOS) knee cleanly dislodges the ball from Nurkic (POR) and he does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Williams III (BOS) is already in Covington's (POR) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Brown (BOS) is already in Covington's (POR) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Covington (POR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Tatum (BOS) on the perimeter.
Tatum (BOS) is bracing for the contact from Nurkic (POR) and releases away from the contact.

After Tatum (BOS) has returned to the floor following his jump shot attempt, Nurkic's (POR) vertical arm makes some contact with Tatum's head.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Williams (BOS) commits a take foul on Covington (POR).
Williams (BOS) never fully gains control of the ball as he attempts to inbound the ball.
Covington (POR) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
Williams III (BOS) commits a take foul on Nurkic (POR).
